<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/62.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Mexico</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-28"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Having received your gratifying response to my inquiry, I have today
                            addressed identic telegrams to the five Central American presidents. I
                            sincerely trust that our concurrent appeal in behalf of peace may have
                            good results.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>